OL,5,Claw
OL,7,FIndeterminate Sentences for Public
OL,8,FProtection were brought in in 2005 by
OL,9,Fthe then Labour government to be
OL,10,Fhanded to a prisoner deemed dangerous
OL,11,Fbut whose crime didn't merit a life
OL,12,Fsentence.
OL,14,FThe whole point was to protect the
OL,15,Fpublic from someone who could cause
OL,16,Fharm. Prisoners were given minimum
OL,17,Fterms they had to serve but crucially
OL,18,F- their detention was unlimited.
OL,20,FThis is an endless sentence. There is
OL,21,Fno release date.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
