OL,3,C'Crushed by a flawed system': More
OL,4,Cthan 2,000 still held under defunct UK
OL,5,Claw
OL,7,FWhen the new sentence became law,
OL,8,Fjudges had to use them. If they didn't
OL,9,Fthey had to explain why.
OL,11,FI've spoken to judges about how and
OL,12,Fwhy IPP sentences were so widely used
OL,13,Ffor petty crimes, like stealing a bike
OL,14,For phone, and I have been told that
OL,15,Fit's because it was easier for a judge
OL,16,Fto use it than it was for them to
OL,17,Fexplain why they weren't going to.
OL,19,FIn 2012 the law was abolished. By that
OL,20,Ftime more than 8,000 people had been
OL,21,Fgiven an IPP sentence.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
