OL,3,C'Crushed by a flawed system': More
OL,4,Cthan 2,000 still held under defunct UK
OL,5,Claw
OL,7,FA Ministry of Justice spokesperson
OL,8,Fsaid: "It is absolutely right that the
OL,9,FIPP sentence was abolished and we have
OL,10,Fsignificantly improved support for
OL,11,Fthese offenders, with greater access
OL,12,Fto rehabilitation and mental health
OL,13,Fsupport.
OL,15,F"By law, the Parole Board considers
OL,16,Fthe case of each IPP prisoner every
OL,17,Ftwo years, judging whether they are
OL,18,Fsafe for release. We consider this an
OL,19,Fimportant safeguard for the public's
OL,20,Fprotection."
